{"word":"φόνιος","slug":"φόνιος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>φόνιος</b></el> <el>(φόνιος, ον,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:φόνος'><el>φόνος</el></a>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>poetic form of <a href='S:φονικός'><el>φονικός</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>of blood, bloody</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>bloody, bloodstained, blood-reeking, murderous</i>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>:—<a href='S:neuter'>neut.</a> <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> as <a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a>, <el>φόνια δερκόμενος</el> <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of actions, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>, <i>bloody, murderous, deadly</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b> <a href='S:confer, compare'>Cf.</a> <el>φοίνιος.</el><p/></div>"}]}